    <briefdescription>
<para>Command that pairs a state transition request with a timer. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Unlike <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1state_1_1commands_1_1StateCommand" kindref="compound">StateCommand</ref>, which triggers a transition immediately during the next flush, <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1state_1_1commands_1_1DelayedStateCommand" kindref="compound">DelayedStateCommand</ref> associates the request with a <ref refid="namespacehelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1timing_1_1types_1ab554d63c8c7c9aa028b0115c23ae01eb" kindref="member">GameTimerId</ref>. The TypedCommandBuffer holds the command until the referenced timer expires, then forwards it to the <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1state_1_1StateManager" kindref="compound">StateManager</ref>.</para>
<para>When the <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1state_1_1StateManager" kindref="compound">StateManager</ref> receives a <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1state_1_1commands_1_1DelayedStateCommand" kindref="compound">DelayedStateCommand</ref> via submit(), it extracts the <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1state_1_1types_1_1StateTransitionRequest" kindref="compound">StateTransitionRequest</ref> and enqueues it as a regular <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1state_1_1commands_1_1StateCommand" kindref="compound">StateCommand</ref> — the timer ID is not retained by the manager.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>StateType</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The state enum type.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
